OBJECTIVE:
The equipment bay's inventory system is partially corrupted. You need to
locate the emergency access code hidden somewhere in this directory.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TASK: Find the Hidden Access Code
─────────────────────────────────
Somewhere in this equipment bay is a hidden file containing an access code.
Find the code and enter it into the verification terminal.

IMPORTANT: Some files are hidden! In Unix systems, files starting with
a dot (.) are hidden from normal directory listings.

Use:  ls -la  to see ALL files, including hidden ones.

When you find the access code, run:
    ./verify <code>

Example: If the code is ABC123, run: ./verify ABC123

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

HINTS:
• ls shows visible files
• ls -la shows ALL files including hidden ones (those starting with .)
• cat <filename> reads a file's contents

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

When complete, you'll unlock access to ENGINEERING to begin system repairs.

